I'm sorry,
A person who is disrespected or whose rights are violated
Apologies are hard to come by.
February 9th
_

WHO Doesn't apologize?

Parents rarely apologize, and even when they do, they always say "for your own good, " implying an accusation that seems ungrateful to their children. One Spring Festival, my parents set me up on a blind date despite my explicit rejection of it, and I was so angry that they said they didn't respect me and didn't want to meet the person they set me up with, and they accused me of being rude. This matter I once sent the friend circle, some people's message said that I should understand parents, to communicate with parents.

The problem isn't me. I can't start an equal dialogue on my own. Even as their children reach adulthood, many parents still maintain a paternalistic approach to parenting, saying, "you don't understand. " "I've eaten more salt than you've walked. ". Parents always think that their pattern is higher, they are right, can not treat and respect their children equally.

The perpetrators of sexual harassment rarely apologize, and they even try to justify themselves by blaming the victim, by saying, "you're underdressed, " "you shouldn't go out at night, " "you seduce me. ".

It is a pity that people who are not respected and whose rights are violated can hardly get an apology. Can lee-w-l get an apology?

Dinner on February 8th
(image courtesy of Guo Jing)

Last night's dinner was stir-fried dried bean curd with celery and rice porridge.

Attended a memorial service for Lee w-l in the evening.

The topic of last night's chat was the end of the world. Someone asked a question: What would you do if the human race were supposed to die out in a day? When discussing this issue, we found that if we only had one day to live, the world would be worse off than it is now, because very few people would continue to serve others. So much of the romantic imagination is hard to implement.

At the end of the world, people will want to do things they haven't done before, because without a future, there will be no ethics. People follow established rules for a social order that rewards those who follow the rules and punishes those who break them.

At the end of the world, there will be desire and there will be fear, and people will want to find someone who is attached to them. Attachment is a bleak and secure relationship in which people are only each other. But finding such a relationship is extremely difficult, and the person we're attached to may not be attached to us in the same way. And how do we deal with fear when we are not able to be with the people we are attached to after a breakdown in traffic?

Some people say, "religious groups should have collective rituals to turn to for comfort. " What about US atheists? Therefore, in order to satisfy everyone's desire, someone proposed that should have a sex party, welcome anyone to join.

The hard part is the food. Some people say you can eat hot pot, but the end of the world when who will look at others in the carnival and their silently choose vegetables, washing vegetables? It can be seen that the most basic human needs can not be separated from society. At the end of the world, very few people get to eat a big meal, most people can only go to the supermarket to get some of their favorite fast food. "We have discovered a human secret, " exclaims one

A Green Road covers the Han River beach on Feb. 9(photo provided by Guo Jing)

Before going to bed, I brushed my phone until February 4, when a public account posted a recording of a call made by a girl from Shandong Province to the mayor of Wuhan's hotline, she expressed her dissatisfaction with the Wuhan Government's handling of the 350 tons of donated vegetables from Shandong Province, saying that the government-government should not sell them, and made suggestions on the government-government distribution process, it is hoped that the supplies will reach the front-line staff in the quickest way possible.

The recording was so moving, she said at the end of the call that she hoped the mayor would give her a reply. At a time when so many people feel powerless, she insists on accountability, an act she knows she can't do. And social change is driven by millions of these people working together.

METASEQUOIA glyptostroboides covered with sweat on Feb. 9(image provided by Guo Jing)

It was a sunny day, and I couldn't resist going out. I don't have a destination. I just want the sun. Out of the community, I think I like that section of the beach, decided to go for a walk. That piece of beach is a run when the chance to run, a few kilometers of distance actually let people have the feeling of the four seasons, there are green in spring, dark green in summer, bright yellow in autumn and yellow in winter. I love it.

On my way to Jiangtan, I passed a small community. There were several people in protective clothing downstairs. One of them took a loudspeaker and called for the people to come down to take food. The two old men picked up the food and went upstairs. To a beach entrance, the administrator sat on a small stool, in front of a bag of melon seeds, melon seeds in a leisurely chipper.

I asked, "are you still afraid of working? "
"there is nothing to be afraid of, " he said, frowning. "It depends on whether your immunity is strong. "
And I can't tell if he's really not worried. I had to tell him to take care.

On both sides of the River Beach Road, Black Lamp Poles are erected every few meters. Every other lamp pole will have an additional black speaker on the lamp pole, these speakers are placed every minute: "In order to effectively implement the city pneumonia command notice requirements, to do a good job in health and epidemic prevention, citizens, visitors friends in public places must wear masks, not in the park pet walk, not spitting, not gathering activities. ". It's kind of a bummer.

Sage on the banks of the Han River on Feb. 9(photo by Guo Jing)

The last time was a few days before the city and friends together, we also use the plant recognition software to check some plants, know the sage and Amur grass. I know very little about the plants I see every day.

The beach is very small, I occasionally pull down the mask to the mouth position, temporarily feel the freedom of breathing. There are greenways along this stretch of River Beach, and we occasionally run into runners. There is a man with a speaker, playing the rhythm of the "men are not bad, women do not love. ". Normally, I would think this song is very vulgar, and now there is a sense of excitement and comedy.

I passed the Yellow Metasequoia, Yellow Golden Chrysanthemum. There was a couple on the road, and the girl wore a helmet over her mask. I walked to the Moon Bay pier, next to the door of the Taurus swimming club has a small blackboard, which reads "water temperature: 7.4 Â°C, February 7, wish: Happy Chinese New Year, covered with sweat refueling. ".

Passing a withered sunflower, one of which is still tenaciously keeping a kind of vitality.

Sunflowers covered with sweat on the Bank of the Yangtze River on Feb. 9(photo by Guo Jing)

I stopped my bicycle and asked a taxi driver playing with his cell phone. "Are you taking patients now? " He said nervously. "We don't take people with fever. We mainly take the sick and the old to buy food and medicine. "
"Did the community arrange it? "
"Yes. "
"What about the hot one? "
"The community will make arrangements. "
"Will the community give out masks? "
"Company issue. "
"What about the SANITIZER? "
"We disinfect people every time we take them in and out. "
I said, "take care, " and rode home.

Wu Han Moon Bay pier on Feb. 9(photo provided by Guo Jing)

10 February
_

These days a lot of people ask me how I am doing. Out of concern, of course, but I'm afraid I can't answer that question.

Who Can Represent Wu Han? WHO's covered in sweat? COVID-19, health care workers, people with chronic diseases (HIV, diabetes, etc.) , the disabled, the elderly, sanitation workers, supermarket cashiers, delivery workers... who are you asking?

Wu Han is in a mess. No one has a clear and complete answer. Apart from a little knowledge of my surroundings and some of the people around me, I get information in the same way as everyone else.

Last night's dinner was sauteed sausage with mushroom and rice porridge. Lentinus edodes was bought on the first day of the city closure, put in the refrigerator for more than 10 days, there is a lentinus edodes into a black red, I still cut it, and some concern, on the Internet to check, see someone said that black lentinus edodes represent moldy, it is best not to eat. As a precaution, I threw out the cut mushrooms.

Too many vegetables are apt to go bad, which will lead to waste. And yet, to survive, we have to stock up.

Dinner on February 9th
(image courtesy of Guo Jing)

Talking to my friends at night. A Guangdong friend ordered take-out and found a "take-out safety card" on the menu, which had the name of the producer, the caterer, the rider, body temperature and hand disinfection. A few friends are at home helping a relative's child with his or her homework. Their patience is greatly challenged, and sometimes they can not help but lose their temper with the child. Some people say: "The child is too kind, the next day will forgive us. " Of course, this is also because the child's life must rely on adults.

When we talk about OCD, some people compulsively pick their pimples, some people scrub the bathroom clean before showering, some people can't stand to sit in their own bed without showering or changing clothes, and some people wash their hands after touching cash. Some people say, "just talking about compulsive behavior reinforces compulsive behavior. " We need nouns to explain our behavior, but we can't let these nouns define us. Just because we have a phase of compulsive behavior and a phase of depression doesn't mean we're always going to be like this. There's a reason for the behavior and the symptoms.

February 9,2009, Guangdong take-away Anxin card (picture provided by Guo Jing)

So, we also talk about why there is a compulsion and why. The person who cleans the bathroom before showering doesn't do so when they're at their parents'house because they don't think they can keep it clean, and they feel more in control in the house they're renting. Some compulsions are about finding some kind of order, a sense of control and security.

A friend is getting an accountant's license in the UK. She says everyone should know the basics of accounting. The UK does its own taxes. It's a way to get involved and understand the country's tax policy, if there is dissatisfaction can also be targeted to make recommendations. And many of us don't know anything about our tax situation, we just passively implement tax policy.

There are so called expertise that we don't feel the need to know, and there are those who try to use professionalism to exclude ordinary people, or even to profit from the information gap. Sure, it takes a long time to get to know every major, but there are people out there who are trying to teach ordinary people science in simple language. There are a lot of people in this outbreak doing science on protection, viruses.

Screenshot from the documentary "Holocaust. "

Today is a cloudy day, I do not go out the demand and desire, feel a little relaxed. I did some filing this morning, and soon two hours passed.

A few days ago, a friend recommended "Holocaust" , which is a simulation of real-life disaster series teaching documentary. I watched the first episode at noon. It was about hijacking airplanes. A person was teaching us how to subdue the hijackers and save ourselves. During the process of tying the hands and feet of the hijackers, "Now to deprive them of their senses, the most important thing at this moment is control, " he said. "We need to deprive them of their ability to control, to see, to speak, even to plug their ears. These people will become completely useless. " I empathized with the robbers.

We are treated as if we were robbers, though not directly deprived of these abilities. However, the information we see and hear is filtered, and we are often silenced. Something about Lee-w-l is already disappearing. Society allows us to censor ourselves, and some people censor others, suggesting that others delete comments that are irrelevant to them and do no harm to anyone.

Friends armed to the teeth on Feb. 10(photo provided by Guo Jing)

In the afternoon, I made an appointment with a friend. She's a girl I met at Wu Han's. I've only met her twice, but she's very congenial. The last time we saw each other was January 19th, but this time it was in a closed city. What a rare gathering this is. She has an electric car, so she came to me. It was drizzling when I went out. She was wearing a mask, a raincoat, a rain mask over her backpack and blue rain boots.

It's a good thing there was no one out there, or I wouldn't have recognized her. We hit it off so well that I didn't invite her to the House and she said we'd sit outside. It's impossible to find an open lounge these days. In the doorway of a dumpling house there is a simple shed under which there is a stool. We sat down and talked, and she wanted to do something for the city, and she wanted to make a video of the sweat in the blockade, and the idea of doing something excited her, and she spoke with joy.

The rain stopped, we went to the river for a while, the river side of the brick cracks have long moss.

Moss in a brick crevice on Feb. 10(image courtesy of Guo Jing)

11 February
_

Many netizens began to care about my diet, which surprised me, because I think I eat well.

When I was a child, every morning and evening is basically steamed vegetable soup, soup is generally white noodle soup, is to use flour and a small amount of water to stir into a solid, then add water to stir it into a liquid, such as water into the mix. My brother and I don't like white noodle soup. We cook rice soup occasionally and put very little rice in it. Noon is basically noodles, the family festival meat to eat. Summer can eat more kinds of vegetables, because rural people will grow their own vegetables. Winter can eat less food, mainly radish, cabbage, potatoes, onions.

Dinner on February 10th
(image courtesy of Guo Jing)

Now even though it is winter, I can eat a variety of vegetables, the basic daily meat to eat. I eat porridge every day is too troublesome, in order to save some time and process of cooking, morning will take the evening porridge cooked together. I like to cook, but it's not easy to spend a lot of time cooking and washing dishes every day. Daily cooking and washing dishes are relatively monotonous and repetitive tasks, and people generally do more creative work will have a sense of value. Learning to cook a new dish in your spare time can be very satisfying, but it's hard to have much fun cooking for a full stomach every day. Many men who occasionally cook can't understand women's complaints about housework.

Poverty is ultimately a matter of unequal distribution. When poverty meets disease, death comes closer. In this epidemic, in each province and city's case fatality rate, the day gate's case fatality rate has been high. February 9, Hubei Province Health Commission first released the provincial cities and states of the case-fatality rate data showed that Tianmen's case-fatality rate is 5.08% , ranking first in the province. There are two triple-a hospitals in Tianmen, and only one comprehensive TRIPLE-A hospital. Tianmen's medical resources are limited, so the risk of death from disease is even higher.

People wait in line at a supermarket on Feb. 11
(image courtesy of Guo Jing)

Last night's dinner was stir-fried dried bean curd with garlic and mushroom.

I still talk to my friends at night. Someone had been taken out of the compound at 34 C, and her family had taken a temperature of 32 c, while others were said to have taken a temperature of 25 c. The person taking the temperature said the lower the better, completely ignoring normal human body temperature standards.

Some people asked what they would do if they unblocked it in the first place. Some people mentioned a joke they saw. Some netizens said they would close it at home for another day, in case the rumor was refuted the next day. Everyone seems to think it makes sense somehow.

Speaking of regrets, some friends regret not giving me enough presents. I said I have always felt pressure to accept gifts, always tied down by the social rules of reciprocity, feeling that I should return gifts, but also very tired to pick gifts, always hope that others can like or use. There's been a lot of talk about it.

Poor people care more about giving gifts, a friend said, "in Eileen Chang's novel, there is a man who goes to a poor family and gets a gift, but when his family is rich, he doesn't do it anymore, and he doesn't worry about being judged. Although people will say he used to bring presents, now it's not polite."

On February 11, Wu Han in the vegetable section of a supermarket
(image courtesy of Guo Jing)

From a young age, people are judging the relationship and grade by other people's gifts, parents will see who sent what gifts, marriage when which relatives with the number of members.

When I was in junior high school, I lived on about 10 yuan a week. I insisted on frugality to buy birthday gifts for my friends. I also expected to receive gifts on my birthday. Many people and former classmates are no longer close, quite social pressure is always in the students when they get married with members. The gift was supposed to be an expression of the heart, but it became a formality.

A friend at a wedding would not go along with the wedding, but would give some special, even handmade gifts, but she will inevitably feel embarrassed.

Friends who are cheap together become rare, and we can haggle over prices when we shop together, and feel a sense of accomplishment when we get something cheap.

A friend who said she bought a $1,000 coat when she graduated now thinks she's in a state of anxiety, but buying expensive clothes doesn't help.

February 11th, the snack area of a supermarket
(image courtesy of Guo Jing)

It was an overcast day, and I had no intention of going out in the morning, when I saw that Wuhan's new pneumonia control and Prevention Headquarters had issued a notice in the middle of the night to close all residential areas throughout the city. Now I have to get out of here. I want to make sure that this is really happening, and what is going on with closed management.

There were three people at the gate in addition to the guards, and no one stopped me as I walked out the door. I went to the supermarket, there were a lot of vegetables, the meat was basically sold out, and the yogurt was half off. When I arrived at the meat counter, the weigh-in crew weighed a few more bags of meat, and I bought three. Some snacks were also sold out. I bought some beef jerky.

This might be my last day out, and I wanted to stay out longer, so I rode my bike around.

Several people line up at the door of the drugstore to buy medicine, keeping a certain distance from each other consciously. Today the volunteers who took the temperature set the table again.

Several vegetable vendors set up shop in front of closed shops and were asked to move to the side of a shop by the Chengguan, at least eight of whom were handling the matter. They just stood by without a single person helping them move their vegetables.

Passing the Jiyuqiao Street Community Health Service Center, there are several people in protective clothing, a man with a CT hand to the people in uniform, I did not hear clearly.

People wait in line outside a pharmacy on Feb. 11
(image courtesy of Guo Jing)

There are still three people outside the compound, one of them in a hazmat suit. When I entered the neighborhood, they said to me, "try to go out less. " I said worriedly, "what about buying food? "
"Buy more. "
"then you have to go out and buy it after you eat it. "
"You may leave. "
"Are you here every day? "
"No, security will check in the city. "

There will always be people for the Vanity Project. It's not just the virus that's locked down, it's people.

When I got home, I divided three bags of meat into 14 portions, and I had meat for the next two weeks.

February 11th, 14 days of meat
(image courtesy of Guo Jing)

I want to be a connection,
I want to be able to connect with more people and act together.

On both sides of the River Beach Road, Black Lamp Poles are erected every few meters. Every other lamp pole will have an additional black speaker on the lamp pole, these speakers are placed every minute: "In order to effectively implement the city pneumonia command notice requirements, to do a good job in health and epidemic prevention, citizens, visitors friends in public places must wear masks, not in the park pet walk, not spitting, not gathering activities. ". It's kind of a bummer.

The beach is very small, I occasionally pull down the mask to the mouth position, temporarily feel the freedom of breathing. There are greenways along this stretch of River Beach, and we occasionally run into runners. There is a man with a speaker, playing the rhythm of the "men are not bad, women do not love. ". ".

Passing a withered sunflower, one of which is still tenaciously keeping a kind of vitality.

I stopped my bicycle and asked a taxi driver playing with his cell phone. "Are you taking patients now? " He said nervously. "We don't take people with fever. We mainly take the sick and the old to buy food and medicine. "
"Did the community arrange it? "
"Yes. "
"What about the hot one? "
"The community will make arrangements. "
"Will the community give out masks? "
"Company issue. "
"What about the SANITIZER? "
"We disinfect people every time we take them in and out. "
I said, "take care, " and rode home.

10 February
_

10 February

These days a lot of people ask me how I am doing. Out of concern, of course, but I'm afraid I can't answer that question.

Who Can Represent Wu Han? WHO's covered in sweat? COVID-19, health care workers, people with chronic diseases (HIV, diabetes, etc.) , the disabled, the elderly, sanitation workers, supermarket cashiers, delivery workers... who are you asking?

Wu Han is in a mess. No one has a clear and complete answer. Apart from a little knowledge of my surroundings and some of the people around me, I get information in the same way as everyone else.

Last night's dinner was sauteed sausage with mushroom and rice porridge. Lentinus edodes was bought on the first day of the city closure, put in the refrigerator for more than 10 days, there is a lentinus edodes into a black red, I still cut it, and some concern, on the Internet to check, see someone said that black lentinus edodes represent moldy, it is best not to eat. As a precaution, I threw out the cut mushrooms.

Too many vegetables are apt to go bad, which will lead to waste. And yet, to survive, we have to stock up.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Dinner on February 9th

Talking to my friends at night. A Guangdong friend ordered take-out and found a "take-out safety card" on the menu, which had the name of the producer, the caterer, the rider, body temperature and hand disinfection. A few friends are at home helping a relative's child with his or her homework. Their patience is greatly challenged, and sometimes they can not help but lose their temper with the child. Some people say: "The child is too kind, the next day will forgive us. " Of course, this is also because the child's life must rely on adults.

When we talk about OCD, some people compulsively pick their pimples, some people scrub the bathroom clean before showering, some people can't stand to sit in their own bed without showering or changing clothes, and some people wash their hands after touching cash. Some people say, "just talking about compulsive behavior reinforces compulsive behavior. " We need nouns to explain our behavior, but we can't let these nouns define us. Just because we have a phase of compulsive behavior and a phase of depression doesn't mean we're always going to be like this. There's a reason for the behavior and the symptoms.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
February 9,2009, Guangdong take-away Anxin card (picture provided by Guo Jing)

So, we also talk about why there is a compulsion and why. The person who cleans the bathroom before showering doesn't do so when they're at their parents'house because they don't think they can keep it clean, and they feel more in control in the house they're renting. Some compulsions are about finding some kind of order, a sense of control and security.

A friend is getting an accountant's license in the UK. She says everyone should know the basics of accounting. The UK does its own taxes. It's a way to get involved and understand the country's tax policy, if there is dissatisfaction can also be targeted to make recommendations. And many of us don't know anything about our tax situation, we just passively implement tax policy.

There are so called expertise that we don't feel the need to know, and there are those who try to use professionalism to exclude ordinary people, or even to profit from the information gap. Sure, it takes a long time to get to know every major, but there are people out there who are trying to teach ordinary people science in simple language. There are a lot of people in this outbreak doing science on protection, viruses.

Screenshot from the documentary "Holocaust. "

Today is a cloudy day, I do not go out the demand and desire, feel a little relaxed. I did some filing this morning, and soon two hours passed.

A few days ago, a friend recommended "Holocaust" , which is a simulation of real-life disaster series teaching documentary. I watched the first episode at noon. It was about hijacking airplanes. A person was teaching us how to subdue the hijackers and save ourselves. During the process of tying the hands and feet of the hijackers, "Now to deprive them of their senses, the most important thing at this moment is control, " he said. "We need to deprive them of their ability to control, to see, to speak, even to plug their ears. These people will become completely useless. " I empathized with the robbers.

We are treated as if we were robbers, though not directly deprived of these abilities. However, the information we see and hear is filtered, and we are often silenced. Something about Lee-w-l is already disappearing. Society allows us to censor ourselves, and some people censor others, suggesting that others delete comments that are irrelevant to them and do no harm to anyone.

In the afternoon, I made an appointment with a friend. She's a girl I met at Wu Han's. I've only met her twice, but she's very congenial. The last time we saw each other was January 19th, but this time it was in a closed city. What a rare gathering this is. She has an electric car, so she came to me. It was drizzling when I went out. She was wearing a mask, a raincoat, a rain mask over her backpack and blue rain boots.

It's a good thing there was no one out there, or I wouldn't have recognized her. We hit it off so well that I didn't invite her to the House and she said we'd sit outside. It's impossible to find an open lounge these days. In the doorway of a dumpling house there is a simple shed under which there is a stool. We sat down and talked, and she wanted to do something for the city, and she wanted to make a video of the sweat in the blockade, and the idea of doing something excited her, and she spoke with joy.

The rain stopped, we went to the river for a while, the river side of the brick cracks have long moss.

11 February
_

11 February

Many netizens began to care about my diet, which surprised me, because I think I eat well.

When I was a child, every morning and evening is basically steamed vegetable soup, soup is generally white noodle soup, is to use flour and a small amount of water to stir into a solid, then add water to stir it into a liquid, such as water into the mix. My brother and I don't like white noodle soup. We cook rice soup occasionally and put very little rice in it. Noon is basically noodles, the family festival meat to eat. Summer can eat more kinds of vegetables, because rural people will grow their own vegetables. Winter can eat less food, mainly radish, cabbage, potatoes, onions.

Now even though it is winter, I can eat a variety of vegetables, the basic daily meat to eat. I eat porridge every day is too troublesome, in order to save some time and process of cooking, morning will take the evening porridge cooked together. I like to cook, but it's not easy to spend a lot of time cooking and washing dishes every day. Daily cooking and washing dishes are relatively monotonous and repetitive tasks, and people generally do more creative work will have a sense of value. Learning to cook a new dish in your spare time can be very satisfying, but it's hard to have much fun cooking for a full stomach every day. Many men who occasionally cook can't understand women's complaints about housework.

Poverty is ultimately a matter of unequal distribution. When poverty meets disease, death comes closer. In this epidemic, in each province and city's case fatality rate, the day gate's case fatality rate has been high. February 9, Hubei Province Health Commission first released the provincial cities and states of the case-fatality rate data showed that Tianmen's case-fatality rate is 5.08% , ranking first in the province. There are two triple-a hospitals in Tianmen, and only one comprehensive TRIPLE-A hospital. Tianmen's medical resources are limited, so the risk of death from disease is even higher.

Last night's dinner was stir-fried dried bean curd with garlic and mushroom.

I still talk to my friends at night. Someone had been taken out of the compound at 34 C, and her family had taken a temperature of 32 c, while others were said to have taken a temperature of 25 c. The person taking the temperature said the lower the better, completely ignoring normal human body temperature standards.

Some people asked what they would do if they unblocked it in the first place. Some people mentioned a joke they saw. Some netizens said they would close it at home for another day, in case the rumor was refuted the next day. Everyone seems to think it makes sense somehow.

Speaking of regrets, some friends regret not giving me enough presents. I said I have always felt pressure to accept gifts, always tied down by the social rules of reciprocity, feeling that I should return gifts, but also very tired to pick gifts, always hope that others can like or use. There's been a lot of talk about it.

Poor people care more about giving gifts, a friend said, "in Eileen Chang's novel, there is a man who goes to a poor family and gets a gift, but when his family is rich, he doesn't do it anymore, and he doesn't worry about being judged. Although people will say he used to bring presents, now it's not polite."

From a young age, people are judging the relationship and grade by other people's gifts, parents will see who sent what gifts, marriage when which relatives with the number of members.

When I was in junior high school, I lived on about 10 yuan a week. I insisted on frugality to buy birthday gifts for my friends. I also expected to receive gifts on my birthday. Many people and former classmates are no longer close, quite social pressure is always in the students when they get married with members. The gift was supposed to be an expression of the heart, but it became a formality.

A friend at a wedding would not go along with the wedding, but would give some special, even handmade gifts, but she will inevitably feel embarrassed.

Friends who are cheap together become rare, and we can haggle over prices when we shop together, and feel a sense of accomplishment when we get something cheap.

A friend who said she bought a $1,000 coat when she graduated now thinks she's in a state of anxiety, but buying expensive clothes doesn't help.

It was an overcast day, and I had no intention of going out in the morning, when I saw that Wuhan's new pneumonia control and Prevention Headquarters had issued a notice in the middle of the night to close all residential areas throughout the city. Now I have to get out of here. I want to make sure that this is really happening, and what is going on with closed management.

There were three people at the gate in addition to the guards, and no one stopped me as I walked out the door. I went to the supermarket, there were a lot of vegetables, the meat was basically sold out, and the yogurt was half off. When I arrived at the meat counter, the weigh-in crew weighed a few more bags of meat, and I bought three. Some snacks were also sold out. I bought some beef jerky.

This might be my last day out, and I wanted to stay out longer, so I rode my bike around.

Several people line up at the door of the drugstore to buy medicine, keeping a certain distance from each other consciously. Today the volunteers who took the temperature set the table again.

Several vegetable vendors set up shop in front of closed shops and were asked to move to the side of a shop by the Chengguan, at least eight of whom were handling the matter. They just stood by without a single person helping them move their vegetables.

Passing the Jiyuqiao Street Community Health Service Center, there are several people in protective clothing, a man with a CT hand to the people in uniform, I did not hear clearly.
